trans-unit.source: The Azure Management Portal provides you with the flexibility to set up a more advanced rule to enable dynamic memberships for groups.
trans-unit.target: The Azure Management Portal provides you with the flexibility to set up a more advanced rule to enable dynamic memberships for groups.

trans-unit.source: To create the advanced rule In the Azure Management Portal, under the group’s Configure tab, select the Advanced rule radio button and then type in your advanced rule in the provided text box.
trans-unit.target: To create the advanced rule In the Azure Management Portal, under the group’s Configure tab, select the Advanced rule radio button and then type in your advanced rule in the provided text box.

trans-unit.source: You can create your advanced rule using the following information.
trans-unit.target: You can create your advanced rule using the following information.

trans-unit.source: The advanced rule that you can create for the dynamic memberships for groups is essentially a binary expression that consists of three parts and results in a true or false outcome.
trans-unit.target: The advanced rule that you can create for the dynamic memberships for groups is essentially a binary expression that consists of three parts and results in a true or false outcome.

trans-unit.source: A complete advanced rule looks similar to this: (leftParameter binaryOperator "RightConstant"), where open and close parenthesis are required for the entire binary expression, double quotes are required for the right constant, and the syntax for the left parameter is user.property.
trans-unit.target: A complete advanced rule looks similar to this: (leftParameter binaryOperator "RightConstant"), where open and close parenthesis are required for the entire binary expression, double quotes are required for the right constant, and the syntax for the left parameter is user.property.

trans-unit.source: An advanced rule can consist of more than one binary expressions separated by the -and, -or, and -not logical operators.
trans-unit.target: An advanced rule can consist of more than one binary expressions separated by the -and, -or, and -not logical operators.

trans-unit.source: The following are examples of a properly constructed advanced rule:
trans-unit.target: The following are examples of a properly constructed advanced rule:

trans-unit.source: For the complete list of supported parameters and expression rule operators, see sections below.
trans-unit.target: For the complete list of supported parameters and expression rule operators, see sections below.

trans-unit.source: The total length of the body of your advanced rule cannot exceed 255 characters.
trans-unit.target: The total length of the body of your advanced rule cannot exceed 255 characters.

trans-unit.source: String and regex operations are case insensitive.
trans-unit.target: String and regex operations are case insensitive.

trans-unit.source: You can also perform Null checks, using $null as a constant, for example, user.department -eq $null.
trans-unit.target: You can also perform Null checks, using $null as a constant, for example, user.department -eq $null.

trans-unit.source: Strings containing quotes " should be escaped using 'character, for example, user.department -eq "Sa`"les".
trans-unit.target: Strings containing quotes " should be escaped using 'character, for example, user.department -eq "Sa`"les".

trans-unit.target: (user.department -eq "value")Property should match one from the supported properties list above.

trans-unit.target: Error: Operator is not supported on attribute.

trans-unit.source: You can now populate members in a group based on the manager attribute of a user.
trans-unit.target: You can now populate members in a group based on the manager attribute of a user.

trans-unit.source: On the Administrator portal, click the Configure tab, and then select ADVANCED RULE.
trans-unit.target: On the Administrator portal, click the Configure tab, and then select ADVANCED RULE.

trans-unit.source: Type the rule with the following syntax: Direct Reports for Direct Reports for {UserID_of_manager}
trans-unit.target: Type the rule with the following syntax: Direct Reports for Direct Reports for {UserID_of_manager}

trans-unit.source: When saving this rule, all users that satisfy the rule will be joined as members of the group.
trans-unit.target: When saving this rule, all users that satisfy the rule will be joined as members of the group.

trans-unit.source: Note that it can take some minutes for the group to initially populate.
trans-unit.target: Note that it can take some minutes for the group to initially populate.
